@fcurella In your fixes #587, you forgot to add the keyword argument min=1 when calling randomize_nb_elements in then sentence method:

        if variable_nb_words:
            nb_words = self.randomize_nb_elements(nb_words, **_min=1_**)

        words = self.words(nb=nb_words, ext_word_list=ext_word_list)
        words[0] = words[0].title()

now I did installed in the right directory but now its giving me printData("argc = ", argc);
printDATA("x",0)

are these something that i need to worry about.

Thanks for replying. Now I'm converting iOS UIImage to cv::Mat, and then convert to array2d.

```objective-c
array2d<bgr_pixel> img;
UIImage *uiimage = [UIImage imageNamed:@"3.png"];
cv::Mat cvimg;
UIImageToMat(uiimage, cvimg);
dlib::assign_image(img, dlib::cv_image<dlib::rgb_alpha_pixel>(cvimg));
```

@href thanks, but I do not agree with the implementation he proposed, so I tried to come up with another solution. Unfortunately the only test case we have is your configuration, so I started from that and I tried to come up with some code. This is why I asked if you could test my code. I think your version file is wrong because it contains integers instead of strings. Why is that? Did you write the file manually? Or did punch write it?

@vovanbo I'm afraid I didn't understand your point, sorry. Date parts are strings because they are formatted with a specific format that returns strings (`'fmt'` is a valid parameter for `strftime()`). Other parts like `IntegerPart` are integers because, well, the name says integer. Storing date version parts as `datetime` objects is, in my opinion, overkill. The `punch_version.py` is intended to be readable, and `datetime` objects are not that clear if you want to represent only one part of the whole date, I think. If you have a counterexample on this, feel free to post it. Please open another issue, however, as this one is dealing with a specific bug.

Overall, I'm afraid I do no understand what we are trying to solve, sorry. If we can come up with a test or a use case that shows a problem, we can perhaps further discuss the issue. I proposed #22 as a solution for a wrong `punch_version.py` file, which contained integers instead of strings. If this is not the problem, as I thought, please can you help me understand the issue?

@kootenpv  I had to hardcode a bugfix for my program because the email would end up making my pandas tables looking completely wrong. But css styles is a true pathological example for why this should be removed, consider:

```
<style>
.classname {
    color: green;
}
</style>
```

will end up getting transformed into
`<style><br>.class {<br>color: green;<br>}<br></style>`

Style tags in email is supported by a surprising number of clients: https://www.campaignmonitor.com/css/style-element/style-in-head/

@swapnilz08 , that is exactly what I am doing ("catch the CommitError exception and do nothing"), but no rebalance in the long term, just ever increasing unbalance.
Now I have 10s of millions records long lags in some partitions while other partitions are up-to-date.

This was not the case before the upgrade. I will have to consider something else, because this completely unacceptable. Basically there is no way to consume a set of messages (instead of all) from Kafka using kafka-python without causing hugely unbalanced partitions overtime, which never recover.

@dpkp , I don't think a simple round-robin is a good idea, as no guarantees that overtime that will balance out the partition offsets.
There would be a need to balance out partition offsets, the randomness of a round-robin consumption will not solve that - leading to unbalanced partition offsets overtime with no way to recover from it.

@Mottie,

Another question I have is if this will work with AJAX content in the table? If so, could you explain if there needs to be any additional configuration?

Could I maybe help motivate with a little PP tip?

@anthonycooray Try [mysqlclient](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/mysqlclient).  It's my fork of this project.
It supports Python 3 and newer MySQL and MariaDB.

@farcepest What do you feel about merging mysqlclient and MySQLdb1?

