Thank you for reporting that issue. The source_ in ThreadedInputSplit and source_ in ImageRecordIter are 2 different things, so that is not a problem, but by the way you worked around it it seems there is some conflict between ThreadedInputSplit and InputSplitShuffle.
I can look into this, but I'm not 100% sure what the priority there should be - I am working on a IO refactor that would enable global shuffling without InputSplitShuffle. On the other hand 0.11 is close and we would probably want to fix it in the meantime before that refactor goes in. 
@piiswrong Any thoughts on that?

_From @michamos on May 11, 2017 14:52_

I am not sure I understand the issue. In `publication_info`, `parent_isbn`, `parent_record` and `parent_record_number` are defined. Maybe we also need `parent_doi` which is not currently defined? 

@annetteholtkamp ?

@larvasapiens - I think there are a number of different scenarios. I personally think that the SDRCategoryEncoder should not store the generated representations and instead use the input value as a seed to the RNG to get deterministic encodings. This would break the ability to "decode" SDRs to categories though so simpler to leave as is for now.

The CategoryEncoder could sometimes be easier to specify the categories at the beginning and sometimes easier to just say how many categories. And the "overflow" bucket sometimes isn't desirable.

So if someone thinks there is a real problem with the existing encoders that can't be solved with a simple mechanism before feeding your values to the encoder then I am open to a proposal. Otherwise it would be good to at least do a documentation update in the code since it looks like it could be improved a lot.

@laem Notice that in the last good commit 8ebbc2e9906688829d3b18c67ea422c1e1ecceb1 before the error comes, the first node of the decomposition is [`salaire_super_brut`](https://github.com/openfisca/openfisca-france/blob/8ebbc2e9906688829d3b18c67ea422c1e1ecceb1/openfisca_france/decompositions/fiche_de_paie_decomposition.xml#L5), which [calls `tehr`](https://github.com/openfisca/openfisca-france/blob/8ebbc2e9906688829d3b18c67ea422c1e1ecceb1/openfisca_france/model/revenus/activite/salarie.py#L730) with a `calculate_divide`.

I think that after that commit, since b7ba469, `tehr` is called directly by the decomposition which uses [`calculate_output`](https://github.com/openfisca/openfisca-core/blob/708bdd784032fda5433a312dd2727956f2878075/openfisca_core/decompositions.py#L25), which is "opt-in". And `salaire_super_brut` decomposition node does not exist anymore.

I hope that it's more clear.

You need to define the one-to-many substitution in a standalone lookup, and then use that lookup contextually. Here's an [example from the specification](http://www.adobe.com/devnet/opentype/afdko/topic_feature_file_syntax.html):

```
lookup CNTXT_LIGS {
     substitute f i by f_i;
     substitute c t by c_t;
 } CNTXT_LIGS;
 
lookup CNTXT_SUB {
     substitute n by n.end;
     substitute s by s.end;
 } CNTXT_SUB;
 
feature test {
     substitute [a e i o u] f' lookup CNTXT_LIGS i' n' lookup CNTXT_SUB;
     substitute [a e i o u] c' lookup CNTXT_LIGS t' s' lookup CNTXT_SUB;
 } test;
```

